Overview
There are four ways Agents can contribute to their Faction‚Äôs victory during the Shared Memories Anomaly Season. Three of these also offer Agents a chance to earn Seasonal Agent Profile Medals through their participation.

Global Shared Link Challenge:
TL;DR: Make and Break Links, and team up for Linkstars in July and August.

Where: Global
When: 12 July 2024 (Fri) 1600 UTC to 5 Aug 2024 (Mon) 1600 UTC. (üóìÔ∏è)

Agents around the world can participate in this Global Challenge by creating and destroying Portal Links, and by taking part in Linkstars (single Portals with hundreds of simultaneously standing Links) during the Challenge dates.

Participating will allow Agents to contribute to their Faction‚Äôs Season victory, as well as unlock the Shared Memories Operation medal (at either a Bronze or Silver tier).

To obtain the medal, Agents must earn a certain amount of Points during the Challenge. An Agent‚Äôs current Point score will be visible on their Agent Profile.

At the end of the Challenge, the Factions will proportionally split 200 Season Points based on how members of their Factions participated.

For more details about how to participate, see the associated section below.

August Daily Bounty Challenge
TL;DR: Complete all your Daily Bounties in August to help your Faction win the Season.

Where: Global
When: 01 Aug 2024 (Thu) 00:00 UTC to 31 Aug 2024 (Sat) 23:59 UTC. (üóìÔ∏è)

Agents around the world can participate in this Global Challenge and help their Factions win the series by regularly completing their Daily Bounties during the month of August. No Season medal can be earned or contributed to by participating in this Challenge. Agents can track their current Bounties Completed and Research Days Completed stats on their Agent Profile.

At the end of the Challenge, the Factions will proportionally split 200 Season Points based on how members of their Factions participated.

For more details about how to participate, see the associated section below.

Shard Skirmishes
TL;DR: Join your Faction to try and win a short Shard based Battle at one of 57 sites around the world across three dates in August and September.

Where and When:

On 24 Aug (Sat), 16:00 to 17:40 local time at 19 AMER (Americas) locations. (üóìÔ∏è)
On 31 Aug (Sat), 16:00 to 17:40 local time at 19 APAC (Asia, Pacific) locations. (üóìÔ∏è)
On 14 Sep (Sat), 16:00 to 17:40 local time at 19 EMEA (Europe, Middle East, Africa) locations. (üóìÔ∏è)
The exact sites will be revealed approximately ten (10) days prior to their event date.

At these events, Agents can take part in a 100-minute-long operation to move Shards along Links. By traversing Shards greater than a defined minimum distance, Points will be scored towards a Faction‚Äôs Season Score. By interacting with Battle Beacons and Hacking Portals where Shards are currently present, Agents will be able to gain the Shared Memories Anomaly medal.

For more details about how to participate in Shard Skirmishes, see the associated section below.

Anomaly Sites
TL;DR: Join a frenetic weekend battle with several competitive components in four cities around the world.

Where and When:

The weekend of 17 August, at two sites: Singapore (üìç, üóìÔ∏è) and Rotterdam(üìç, üóìÔ∏è).
The weekend of 21 September, at two sites: Hakodate (üìç, üóìÔ∏è) and Seattle(üìç, üóìÔ∏è).
At these Sites, Agents can take part in multiple score-based competitive operations, such as Urban and Stealth Ops, Portal Battles and Shard Operations (Urban and Stealth Ops availability may vary site to site). The outcome of these events will contribute to a Faction‚Äôs Season Score. Interacting with Battle Beacons at Anomaly sites will enable Agents to earn the Shared Memories Anomaly medal.

For more details about how to participate in Anomalies, see the associated section below.

Shared Memories Anomaly Season Scoring
The final outcome of the Shared Memories Anomaly Season will be based on the total Season Score accrued by each Faction from all of the above components, and the Faction with the higher final score will claim the Season.

For more details about how each component will contribute to the Season Score, see the associated sections for each component below.

